</p>
<h2>
    Trout Fishing Regulations and License Requirements
</h2>
<p>
    To fish legally in Oregon:
</p>
<ul>
    <li>
        <strong>Angling license</strong> is required for ages 12 and up.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Harvest limits</strong>: Typically 5 trout per day in stocked waters.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Catch-and-release only</strong> in many wild streams—check signage and regulations.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Barbless hook</strong> rules apply in certain protected streams.
    </li>
</ul>
<p>
